HEADWORD: Intubation
<hw>In`tu*ba"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>tube</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The
introduction of a tube into an organ to keep it open, as into the larynx
in croup.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

